Fantastic experience.   I found Johnson roofing using the YELP app, and the reviews were great.   I am a Canadian with a seasonal home I visit several times a year in Gilbert. Finding quality trades people off the internet is a little nerve wracking. You are never sure if the reviews are totally legit!   So I came for a visit to my humble abode this summer and alarmingly found a few tiles from the corner of my roof lying on the ground. It looked minor, but I don't have a ladder tall enough to go see what was happening!   I did my Yelp and Google search for local roofers, and came across Johnson roofing. I spoke with a friendly office person who asked me to simply send some pictures and they had a $250 special that would likely cover the minor repairs. They wouldn't need to come and look - the pictures would be enough information and they could book a time based on the pictures I sent.   So off to the yard with my trusty iPhone and zip-a-da-do-da I emailed the pictures. It was a Friday afternoon, and I was told it may take until early the next week to confirm the job. Tuesday I simply received an email saying that they would be by Thursday at 1pm.  I was out enjoying a beautiful golf day, and when I was done there was an email with a dozen pictures showing the extensive work they completed fixing much more than just a couple broken tiles!!   Very impressive service Johnson Roofing!! Thank you for that!

